miscConds.notes:
The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by a risk and needs assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions. Follow through with any recommendations regarding criminal thinking. Must participate in and successfully complete sex offender management programming. Must submit to any other recommended evaluations or treatment as recommended by your probation agent.

7 days jail credit, if revoked.
Restitution to be paid through your probation agent.

If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged or terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of any restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Must pay all costs of supervision and court ordered financial obligations during the term of probation. 

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment.

Defendant shall have no contact, directly or indirectly, either personally, by mail, telephone or through any other person or by any other means with non-relative minor females except incidental, in public places, or with the supervision of the minor's parents/guardians.

10:57 AM Defendant Darin J. Meddaugh in court.  Attorney Emily Hynek in court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Matthew Krische in court for Darin J. Meddaugh. State in compliance with victim rights.  Defendant enters a plea of Guilty to Count 1 and Count 2. 
Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Felony warnings given.  He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Diversion agreement on Count 1 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child contrary to 948.02(2), 4th Degree Sexual Assault contrary to 940.225(3m).  

Victims mother makes a statement. Defendant exercised his right to allocution. 

Joint recommendation: With hold judgment/follow 3 year Diversion Agreement to Count 1. Count 2, withhold sentence , 2 year probation. Payment of restitution. Six months conditional jail imposed and stayed for use by the agent in case of violation. Obtain sex offender assessment. No contact with non-relative minor females except incidental, in public places, or with the supervision of the minor's parents/guardian. 7 days credit, if revoked.   $301.86 requested amount of restitution

Court reviewed the proposed diversion agreement. Defendant stated he understood the agreement and believes he can comply with the requirements. Court withholds entry of judgment approves the diversion agreement with terms for period of 36 months.    

Court adopts the joint recommendation: Court with holds judgment. Follow Diversion Agreement to Count 1. Count 2, withhold sentence , 2 year probation.  Payment of restitution. 6 month jail sentence,  Six months conditional jail imposed and stayed for use by the agent in case of violation  Sex offender assessment and follow through with any recommended treatment. No contact with non-relative minor females except incidental, in public places, or with the supervision of the minor's parents/guardian.  7 days credit, if revoked.   Pay $301.86 requested amount of restitution.  risk and needs assessment. Follow thru with and recommendations regarding Criminal thinking. Pay costs through probation. 

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen and report for booking. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment. 

Report to probation by 2 pm today.
